SIMPLE: unmoor
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unmoor
<hw>Un*moor"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>moor</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>To cause to ride with one anchor less than before, after having
been moored by two or more anchors.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>To loose
from anchorage. See <er>Moor</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unmoor</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unmoor
<hw>Un*moor"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To weigh anchor.</def>
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unmoral</ent>⟦br⟧
